<Initials>R</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Department of Neurology, Erciyes University Faculty of Medicine, Kayseri, Turkey. Electronic address: recep.baydemir@gmail.com.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN=\"Y\"><LastName>De&#x11f;irmenci</LastName><ForeName>Y&#x131;ld&#x131;z</ForeName><Initials>Y</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Department of Neurology, D&#xfc;zce University Faculty of Medicine, D&#xfc;zce, Turkey. Electronic address: ydegir@gmail.com.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN=\"Y\"><LastName>Ba&#x15f;ak</LastName><ForeName>Ay&#x15f;e Nazl&#x131;</ForeName><Initials>AN</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Department of Molecular Biology and Genetics, Ko&#xe7; University, Istanbul, Turkey. Electronic address: nbasak@ku.edu.tr.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author></AuthorList><Language>eng</Language><PublicationTypeList><PublicationType UI=\"D016422\">Letter</PublicationType></PublicationTypeList><ArticleDate DateType=\"Electronic\"><Year>2026</Year><Month>03</Month><Day>04</Day></ArticleDate></Article><MedlineJournalInfo><Country>Netherlands</Country><MedlineTA>Clin Neurol Neurosurg</MedlineTA><NlmUniqueID>7502039</NlmUniqueID><ISSNLinking>0303-8467</ISSNLinking></MedlineJournalInfo><CitationSubset>IM</CitationSubset><KeywordList Owner=\"NOTNLM\"><Keyword MajorTopicYN=\"N\">Amyotrophic lateral sclerosis</Keyword><Keyword MajorTopicYN=\"N\">Case series</Keyword><Keyword MajorTopicYN=\"N\">FTD-ALS spectrum</Keyword><Keyword MajorTopicYN=\"N\">Frontotemporal dementia</Keyword><Keyword MajorTopicYN=\"N\">Genetic mutation</Keyword><Keyword MajorTopicYN=\"N\">VCP gene</Keyword></KeywordList><CoiStatement>Conflicts of interest None declared.</CoiStatement></MedlineCitation><PubmedData><History><PubMedPubDate PubStatus=\"received\"><Year>2026</Year><Month>1</Month><Day>11</Day></PubMedPubDate><PubMedPubDate PubStatus=\"revised\"><Year>2026</Year><Month>3</Month><Day>3</Day></PubMedPubDate><PubMedPubDate PubStatus=\"accepted\"><Year>2026</Year><Month>3</Month><Day>3</Day></PubMedPubDate><PubMedPubDate PubStatus=\"pubmed\"><Year>2026</Year><Month>3</Month><Day>6</Day><Hour>19</Hour><Minute>44</Minute></PubMedPubDate><PubMedPubDate PubStatus=\"medline\"><Year>2026</Year><Month>3</Month><Day>6</Day><Hour>19</Hour><Minute>44</Minute></PubMedPubDate><PubMedPubDate PubStatus=\"entrez\"><Year>2026</Year><Month>3</Month><Day>6</Day><Hour>18</Hour><Minute>1</Minute></PubMedPubDate></History><PublicationStatus>ppublish</PublicationStatus><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">41791136</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"doi\">10.1016/j.clineuro.2026.109381</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"pii\">S0303-8467(26)00073-9</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></PubmedData></PubmedArticle><PubmedArticle><MedlineCitation Status=\"MEDLINE\" Owner=\"NLM\" IndexingMethod=\"Automated\"><PMID Version=\"1\">41791354</PMID><DateCompleted><Year>2026</Year><Month>06</Month><Day>10</Day></DateCompleted><DateRevised><Year>2026</Year><Month>06</Month><Day>10</Day></DateRevised><Article PubModel=\"Print-Electronic\"><Journal><ISSN IssnType=\"Electronic\">1873-3573</ISSN><JournalIssue CitedMedium=\"Internet\"><Volume>305</Volume><PubDate><Year>2026</Year><Month>Aug</Month><Day>01</Day></PubDate></JournalIssue><Title>Talanta</Title><ISOAbbreviation>Talanta</ISOAbbreviation></Journal><ArticleTitle>A multi-platform analytical strategy for Atractylodes lancea authentication: Fusion of stable isotope, elemental, chromatographic, and spectroscopic profiles.</ArticleTitle><Pagination><StartPage>129603</StartPage><MedlinePgn>129603</MedlinePgn></Pagination><ELocationID EIdType=\"doi\" ValidYN=\"Y\">10.1016/j.talanta.2026.129603</ELocationID><ELocationID EIdType=\"pii\" ValidYN=\"Y\">S0039-9140(26)00258-4</ELocationID><Abstract><AbstractText Label=\"BACKGROUND &amp; AIMS\" NlmCategory=\"OBJECTIVE\">The quality and market value of the medicinal herb Atractylodes lancea (AL) are critically dependent on its variety, geographical origin, and production mode. To combat adulteration and ensure efficacy, we developed a novel multi-platform analytical strategy integrated with machine learning to establish a robust traceability model for variety discrimination, geographical origin determination, and production mode identification of AL and identify the key chemical indicators responsible for its authentication.</AbstractText><AbstractText Label=\"RESULTS\" NlmCategory=\"RESULTS\">Significant differences were found in trace element concentrations and isotopic ratios among samples. AL's main flavors were spicy, sweet, and fruity, with terpenoids as key aroma contributors. OPLS-DA identified key indicators for tracing AL's variety, including eleven trace elements (e.g., V, Al) and eight volatile compounds (e.g., &#x3b2;-Sesquiphellandrene, 2-Pinen-10-ol). For tracing AL origins, ten trace elements (e.g., Sr, Cr), two stable isotopes (&#x3b4;<sup>13</sup>C, &#x3b4;<sup>15</sup>N), five flavor components (e.g., 2-ethyl-3,6-dimethylpyrazine, 2-Pentadecanone), and twenty-six volatile components (e.g., &#x3b3;-Gurjunene, &#x3b2;-Bisabolene) were identified. Furthermore, three trace elements (Mg, Li and Pb), two isotopes (&#x3b4;<sup>13</sup>C and &#x3b4;<sup>15</sup>N), two flavor components (&#x3b1;-Pinene and n-Nonylcyclohexane), and two volatile components (&#x3b1;-Copaene and &#x3b1;-Curcumene) were identified as key indicators for tracing AL's production modes. Finally, among the nine machine learning algorithms evaluated, LightGBM demonstrated superior performance, achieving a traceability accuracy of 95.28&#xa0;&#xb1;&#xa0;3.01%.</AbstractText><AbstractText Label=\"CONCLUSION\" NlmCategory=\"CONCLUSIONS\">The multi-platform data fusion strategy presents a thorough and dependable approach to quality control for Atractylodes lancea. This method establishes a precise, efficient, and adaptable framework, demonstrating substantial potential for application to other high-value botanicals and complex natural products.</AbstractText><CopyrightInformation>Copyright &#xa9; 2026 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.</CopyrightInformation></Abstract><AuthorList CompleteYN=\"Y\"><Author ValidYN=\"Y\"><LastName>Gan</LastName><ForeName>YiFu</ForeName><Initials>Y</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>School of Pharmacy, Nanjing University of Chinese Medicine, Nanjing, 210023, People's Republic of China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN=\"Y\"><LastName>Ju</LastName><ForeName>Ruixin</ForeName><Initials>R</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Wuxi Hospital of Traditional Chinese Medicine, Wuxi, 214071, People's Republic of China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN=\"Y\"><LastName>Peng</LastName><ForeName>Yongbo</ForeName><Initials>Y</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>International Center for Isotope Effects Research, Nanjing University, Nanjing, 210023, People's Republic of China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN=\"Y\"><LastName>Xiao</LastName><ForeName>Shan</ForeName><Initials>S</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>School of Pharmacy, Nanjing University of Chinese Medicine, Nanjing, 210023, People's Republic of China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN=\"Y\"><LastName>Qiu</LastName><ForeName>Rongli</ForeName><Initials>R</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>School of Pharmacy, Nanjing University of Chinese Medicine, Nanjing, 210023, People's Republic of China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN=\"Y\"><LastName>Wang</LastName><ForeName>Sheng</ForeName><Initials>S</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>State Key Laboratory for Quality Ensurance and Sustainable Use of Dao-di Herbs, National Resource Center for Chinese Materia Medica, China Academy of Chinese Medical Sciences, Beijng, 100700, People's Republic of China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN=\"Y\"><LastName>Zhang</LastName><ForeName>Yan</ForeName><Initials>Y</Initi